# Finding 054
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Template shell duplicates base app files
- File + line(s): `packages/tooling/create-app/templates/base-shell/app.scripts.config.mjs:1-3`, `apps/base-app/app.scripts.config.mjs:1-3`, `packages/tooling/create-app/templates/base-shell/eslint.config.mjs:1-10`, `apps/base-app/eslint.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/tooling/create-app/templates/base-shell/server/lib/runtimeEnv.js:1-16`, `apps/base-app/server/lib/runtimeEnv.js:1-16`
- Why it can drift/fail: The create-app template shell is an exact copy of the base app. Any change to the base app requires a manual mirror into the template or new apps will be created with stale config.
- Concrete impact: Generated apps can be out-of-date with the canonical base app configuration, leading to confusing drift for new projects.
- Exact remediation: Make the template reference a single source of truth (e.g., generate from `apps/base-app` or share a small config package) instead of duplicating files.

## Resolution
- Justification: Template files are actively being rewritten, and this finding targets create-app template content. Per instruction, avoid template/client-side work to prevent conflicts.
- Revisit signal: After the template rewrite lands and stabilizes, evaluate consolidating base-shell files to reference the base app or a shared config package.

